    "\n",

    "## Load synthetic data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4ecacf8b-e536-4b67-a67c-fb1dbde54fae",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Synthetic d13C signal and data\n",
    "Use the same d13C signal and observations as in Fig. 8"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "8e4c42ff-859e-4316-90d4-6066727df7c4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",

       "<Figure size 500x300 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "age_vector = np.arange(400, 450, 0.25)\n",
    "amplitude = [3, -4, 6, -2]\n",
    "d13c_signal = stratmc.synthetics.make_excursion(\n",
    "    age_vector,\n",
    "    amplitude,\n",
    "    excursion_duration=[10, 8, 10, 5],\n",
    "    rising_time=[0.3, 0.7, 0.9, 0.3],\n",
    "    smooth=True,\n",
    "    smoothing_factor=2,\n",
    "    rate_offset=True,\n",
    "    seed=7,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "d13c_signal = gaussian(np.flip(d13c_signal), 3)\n",
    "\n",
    "signal_dict = {}\n",
    "signal_dict[\"d13c\"] = d13c_signal\n",
    "\n",
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(5, 3))\n",
    "ax = fig.gca()\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.plot(age_vector, d13c_signal, color=\"indianred\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.invert_xaxis()\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"Age (Ma)\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"d13C\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "d717964d-5690-41f9-b174-7b8b56697d29",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "sample_df = stratmc.data.load_object(\n",
    "    \"data/Fig8_synthetic_sample_df_multiproxy_modified\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "ages_df = stratmc.data.load_object(\"data/Fig8_synthetic_ages_df_multiproxy_modified\")\n",
    "\n",
    "sections = np.unique(sample_df[\"section\"].values)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "41b51fbf-7974-4619-aca0-8b91979c7448",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## HSGP approximation: Trial 1 \n",
    "First, we try the HSGP approximation with $m$ and $c$ parameters optimized for the full range of the lengthscale prior. Later, we'll narrow down the likely range of lengthscales to reduce $m$ and $c$, which will speed up sampling time."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "34cc2e30-a93f-45a0-82a0-2b1b8c2f31cd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Configure the HSGP approximation\n",
    "Here, we build an inference model and sample the prior in order to estimate the full range of possible lengthscales. We'll then use this range to estimate optimal values for the $m$ and $c$ parameters for the HSGP approximation using `pymc.gp.hsgp_approx.approx_hsgp_hyperparams`. \n",
    "\n",
    "Note that the recommended values might vary slightly for different sets of prior draws. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "25de762a-9f37-4ea7-ab22-7dd11c1716f1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Build unapproximated GP model\n",
    "proxies = [\"d13c\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "model, gp = stratmc.model.build_model(\n",
    "    sample_df,\n",
    "    ages_df,\n",
    "    proxies=proxies,\n",
    "    ls_dist=\"Wald\",\n",
    "    ls_min=3,  # minimum RBF kernel lengthscale\n",
    "    ls_mu=10,  # mean of Wald distribution used as RBF kernel lengthscale prior\n",
    "    ls_lambda=25,  # lambda of Wald distribution used as RBF kernel lengthscale prior\n",
    "    offset_type=\"section\",  # per-section offset with default prior\n",
    "    noise_type=\"section\",  # per-section noise with default prior\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "526e27e6-c76b-440d-9929-4718cd186cfa",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Sampling: [gp_ls_unshifted_d13c]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Sample the model prior\n",
    "ls_names = []\n",
    "for proxy in proxies:\n",
    "    ls_names.append(\"gp_ls_\" + proxy)\n",
    "\n",
    "with model:\n",
    "    prior = pm.sample_prior_predictive(draws=100000, var_names=ls_names)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "bca67c7d-cd91-4ae8-add2-a3faaf534130",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Recommended smallest number of basis vectors (m) for d13c :  137\n",
      "Recommended smallest scaling factor (c) for d13c :  12.3\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# using the prior draws to estimate the range of possible lengthscales, then calculate optimal HSGP parameters\n",
    "proxy = \"d13c\"\n",
    "\n",
    "ls_min = np.min(az.extract(prior.prior)[\"gp_ls_\" + proxy].values.ravel())\n",
    "ls_max = np.max(az.extract(prior.prior)[\"gp_ls_\" + proxy].values.ravel())\n",
    "\n",
    "m, c = pm.gp.hsgp_approx.approx_hsgp_hyperparams(\n",
    "    x_range=[np.min(ages_df[\"age\"].values), np.max(ages_df[\"age\"].values)],\n",
    "    lengthscale_range=[ls_min, ls_max],\n",
    "    cov_func=\"expquad\",\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Recommended smallest number of basis vectors (m) for\", str(proxy), \": \", m)\n",
    "print(\"Recommended smallest scaling factor (c) for\", str(proxy), \": \", np.round(c, 1))\n",
    "\n",
    "hsgp_m = m\n",
    "hsgp_c = c\n",
    "\n",
    "del prior"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f0cf5ef5-e2b1-4ce8-930f-5e7c668a728a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Build model using the HSGP approximation with the recommended $m$ and $c$ parameters\n",
    "\n",
    "To load the inference results used to produce Fig. B1b, skip to [Load the inference results (HSGP, trial 1)](#Load-the-inference-results-(HSGP,-trial-1)). "
   ]

    ")"
   ]
